fields.title: The Complete Guide on Microsoft SharePoint Workspace
fields.body:
A Microsoft SharePoint Workspace for Better Team Collaboration

One of the best ways to help your team collaborate and share documents and files seamlessly and effectively in Microsoft 365 is to create a Microsoft SharePoint workspace. Once there is a SharePoint site, then all the files and documents in it can be synchronized and accessed on a desktop both online and offline. This is the most important aspect of the workspace. The SharePoint document lists and libraries can be synced too. People from different parts of the world, irrespective of where they are, can access the SharePoint workspace from their personal computers.

The team members can edit the content of the workspace, add new content and then synchronize it back. The changes one makes to the workspace are automatically synchronized to the SharePoint server so that anyone who has access can see them. This is highly useful for people working in teams. When a user disconnects from the internet, the changes made in the workspace are stored locally until the connection is reset and then it automatically syncs with the server. The main benefit of the SharePoint workspace is that you can work with the team effortlessly and coordinate the activities without delay and extra effort.

Previously known as Microsoft Office Groove, the Microsoft SharePoint workspace is now one of the most popular project management and intranet solution both for teams and large enterprises as a whole. The offline experience you get is awesome with extra features and capabilities being added regularly by Microsoft. In short, SharePoint Workspace gets you the best quality output when collaborating with a team and synchronize and share files and documents.

A Deeper Look at the Microsoft SharePoint Workspace

Work Together Effectively

SharePoint workspace makes it highly effective for teams to come together and share ideas. You no longer need to worry about ideas being lost with SharePoint Workspace getting the team together.

Sync With SharePoint Sites

With just a few clicks, you can synchronize the documents and libraries to your personal computer. Once you have worked through them you can again sync them back to the server. You take control of the full activity.

Take Some or All of your SharePoint Site Content Offline

You are free to take the content of the SharePoint site to your personal computer and edit them. This included lists, libraries, documents, etc. It is very easy to create a workspace from a SharePoint site, or you can directly launch the workspace launch bar.

Direct Access to the Folder

By making use of Windows Explorer, you can access the SharePoint site files in a folder. You can add other content in the folder. The SharePoint Workspace synchronized the files to the SharePoint site automatically.

Easy Search of all the Spaces

Using the search feature in Windows, you can easily search the Workspaces in your computer and even customize the queries to get the exact spaces. This makes the workspace easy to access and less complicated.

Access Your Work Anywhere

Super Easy Log-in

You do not need to log in to the SharePoint Workspace with a username and password. Instead, the login credentials you use for the Windows login will be used for the workspace automatically.

Mobile-Friendly Use

Even if you are traveling, you can use the SharePoint Workspace with your smartphone and edit, add, or save the files and documents. This makes SharePoint workspace your friend wherever you are without ever worrying about updates and edits you have to make.

Give Wings to Your Ideas

Easy Access to All the Tools you Need

The SharePoint Workspace comes with highly useful features and you can get access to them at the customizable and enhanced ribbon in the workspace. Without searching for the tool, what you need is right at your fingertips.

Work Securely with the Documents

There is a chance that a team member of yours may be working on the same document as you are. So, to avoid any conflict, you can always lock the document you are working on. This helps you to fully edit and save the document as your own. The facility is just a click away.

Move Between Your Workspaces with Ease

It is so easy to move from one workspace to another. You can use the launch bar to access all your workspaces without any difficulty. You can always see what is unread on any workspace, what is the latest news, updates, etc from the launch bar.

The Microsoft Office Backstage View

The Microsoft office backstage view helps you to customize and make the SharePoint workspace attractive and improve your working experience. You need good experience working on documents and the Microsoft Office Backstage view helps you achieve that. Everything is just a click of a button away with an easy-to-access toolbar and help options available for you. Customize the workspace and get the most out of your work.

All In One Communications

All your contacts lists are available on the launch bar for the workspace and you will see who is available and who is not. You can get in touch with the available contacts through instant messages and voice calls. This makes it highly convenient and easy to interact with. A presence icon is displayed on the contacts and you just need to hover over the contact and a conversation can be initiated.

Improved Translation and Language Settings

The user can customize and enjoy the multilingual language experience with the help of display, helps, and translation tools. You are free to set your interests and preferences and use the SharePoint workspace in the best possible manner. Whatever be your need, the SharePoint Workspace has got you covered.

The Different Kinds of Workspaces in SharePoint Workspace

There are three types of workspaces in SharePoint Workspace namely SharePoint workspaces, Groove Workspaces, and shared folders.

  • SharePoint workspaces help you to create a separate workspace entirely for you. Once you finish doing all the work the workspace is synchronized with the SharePoint site. The only person included in this type of workspace is the creator.
  • Groove Workspace is an earlier release of the SharePoint workspace and includes a lot of productivity tools that can be added as needs and usually has two or more people join via invitation.
  • A shared folder is a typical kind of Groove Workspace that enables you to share the contents of the folder in the Windows file system.

The Sections of a SharePoint Workspace

  • Synchronized document libraries
  • Synchronized SharePoint Lists
  • Libraries or lists not supported in the SharePoint Workspace. Usually, a link is provided to access these.
  • The content in the document library.

How to Create a SharePoint Workspace

Creating a SharePoint Workspace is easy. The best way is to go to the SharePoint site and then synchronize it with your computer. All the available libraries and lists will be downloaded to the new workspace.

  1. Open the web browser and go to the SharePoint site.
  2. Click on-site actions.
  3. Then click Sync to SharePoint Workspace.
  4. Now, in the dialog box that shows sync to SharePoint Workspace, click OK.
  5. The download starts, and when the download finishes, click open workspace or close.

How To Create a SharePoint Workspace by Syncing a Selected Library or List

There are times when you only need to synchronize a specific list or library into the workspace. This is important as it helps you save a lot of time rather than downloading from other libraries and lists.

  1. Open the web browser and go to the SharePoint site.
  2. Select the library or list that you need to synchronize to your computer.
  3. Do any one of the below:
    • If you had selected a list, then click lists under list tools.
    • If you had selected a library, then click, library under library tools.
  4. Next, in the ribbon of the SharePoint, in the connect and export group, click, sync to SharePoint Workspace.
  5. Now click Ok.
  6. The download will begin and once it is complete, click open workspace or close.

Wrapping Up

Microsoft SharePoint Workspace is one of the best tools to access all the important data in your computer and then sync it back to the SharePoint site Libraries and lists. Workspace makes it extremely easy and convenient for the user to work privately and without distractions.

The SharePoint Workspace makes it much easier for one to work with teams since both online and offline access is available. You can use your workspace on the go with the help of a mobile device and edit, save and add stuff and it will not get simpler than that.

Team members can access the files you have worked and the automatic synchronization makes everything super convenient. With many Microsoft office tools available; SharePoint workspace is one to check out if you are working as part of a team. The user-friendly interface and tools help you navigate easily and do the work in less time. It is a new advancement in technology and teamwork, and with years going by, Microsoft is adding new awesome features to the Workspace and let us hope for some exciting updates soon.

fields.intro: In this tutorial, you will learn about what is Microsoft Visio, what functions and tools it has, and how to use it
fields.title: Visualize Your Company: A Microsoft Visio Tutorial
fields.body:
In this tutorial, you will learn about what is Microsoft Visio, what functions and tools it has, and how to use it. In simple words, Microsoft Visio is a diagramming tool that will help you create diagrams that are complex as well as simple. You can use it to draw vector diagrams and business charts and graphs to make your workflow smooth and appealing. There are many inbuilt templates available in Visio to make it easy to use.

You can use this diagramming tool to insert shapes, connectors, and text into your diagrams and make them stand out. You will find a ton of prebuilt shapes and templates that you can use. Whatever be your drawing need, Visio has got you covered. In this Microsoft Visio Tutorial, we will cover more details about the Microsoft Visio app that will be useful to you.

What Makes Visio Exciting

So why Visio? After all, aren’t there already tons of tools to make diagrams? Wouldn’t you be able to do all the same things with Microsoft’s existing apps like Excel and PowerPoint anyway? As you will see in this tutorial, Visio is Microsoft’s one stop solution to create a comprehensive process flowcharts for businesses.

Real World Applications of Visio for Businesses

Organizational Chart

Perhaps the most common use for Visio. Organizational charts are a great way to convey a company's structure. Not only, do they show the structure of various departments, their roles, functions, and responsibilities. A detailed organizational chart can even include the name of key people, contact information, or even outline the relationship between the different departments.

With Visio, creating an organizational chart is as easy as having a list of names, departments, and other relevant information, importing the data into Visio, and pulling them into place. You can then draw different relationships and charts with the data. If you ever need to update the chart, just update the excel worksheet, and update the data in Visio.

Business Process Diagrams

Another popular use for Visio is to make business process flowcharts. In today’s business world, business process flow charts are becoming a standard both for internal and external stakeholders. As consultants, we also like to work with these kinds of flowcharts so both we and our clients understand exactly what our goals are, and what are the processes to get us there. In these diagrams, we can convey as much detail as we need on each process or strategy, and still make it easy to understand.

This type of flowchart is a standard feature in all versions of Visio. It also includes many different process workflow templates based on a company’s needs. Depending on what kind of processes you want to outline, you can create anything from a simple flowchart to a comprehensive BPMN or value stream map.

System Maps

Business owners are not engineers. They do not necessarily understand how different systems and software work with each other. So, they are often surprised last minute when an important business process stops working because a system that they have never even heard of goes offline. Worse, they might not even know who they can contact to repair the defective system.

A system map is the perfect solution to help every team member, both technical and non-technical, to understand what technology powers their processes, and how to service it. Like the previous two charts, this relationship can easily be drawn simply by linking the systems and processes flowcharts appropriately.

Key Features

Work From Anywhere, Anytime

With Microsoft Visio, you can work from anywhere in the world and at any time you like. All you need is to open the Visio app and get your drawings in place. The platform is so easy to use that you make easy changes and adjustments with a click of a button.

The Ultimate App for Diagramming

If you are someone looking to creates some flowcharts and diagrams, then Visio is the best option. Whatever be your diagram needs, Visio provides the solution. You can save your diagrams to your computer and access them whenever you need them. You can create flowcharts, organizational charts, floor plans, brainstorming, network diagrams, etc in this all-in-one solution app.

Real-Time Collaboration

Create unique diagrams and author them and share them with your team for easy collaboration. This helps you convey the message to your team easily and efficiently. Use Visio inside the Microsoft team to make it even more convenient and productive.

Microsoft 365 and Visio

You can leverage the power of Microsoft 365 in the Visio app. With features inbuilt to help you access the power of Microsoft 365, Visio becomes more exciting and interesting. Once inside the Microsoft teams, you can create, edit, and collaborate on Visio diagrams.

Full Privacy and Enterprise-Grade Security

Visio has almost the same security features as the Microsoft 365 apps. So, you can be sure that your data is secure and private. Microsoft makes your privacy fully protected and gives you confidence for using the app.

How to Use Microsoft Visio

Now let’s see how to use Visio in this Microsoft Visio Tutorial. If you are a business and want to add some interesting and informative diagrams to your presentation or an individual who wants to make a presentation, then Microsoft Visio is for you.

Let’s start by looking at the different components of Visio:

The Various Visio File Types

We will come to know about the various Visio file types in this Microsoft Visio Tutorial. The following are the different file types in MS Visio.

  • VSD (Visio Drawing) – This is the Visio binary file format extension. It is used to save diagrams and flowcharts document files.
  • VST (Visio Template) – This type of file extension is related to Visio templates.
  • VST (Visio Template) – This type of file extension is related to Visio templates.
  • VST (Visio Stencil) - The file extension is associated with smart shapes (Stencils). The file is available in binary Visio document format.
  • VST (Visio Web Drawing) – This file extension is associate with all the web drawing in Microsoft Visio.

The Major Components of Visio

Now let’s come to the components in this Microsoft Visio Tutorial. The components of Visio can be classified into:

Stencils

Stencils have a collection of similar shapes. You will see stencils on the left-hand side of the drawing page. You can also save your shapes into stencils for future reference and usage. This makes them convenient to use.

The Quick Access Toolbar

The quick access toolbar gives you a list of commands for easy use. You can also add commands that you use often and in need. It is a helpful option in Microsoft Visio.

The Ribbon

The ribbon is an important panel in Visio that helps you to get access to all the tabs and their groupings. Under each tab, you will see drop-down lists of important and useful items. You can select the item you want to use. To complete your task in Visio, you need these commands.

The File Tab

Clicking on the File tab takes you to the backstage view in Visio. Here you can see the various actions and functions you can perform such as saving the file, closing, creating, printing, sharing, etc. The file option is very important in Visio. In this place, you can see the properties of the file and can remove personal information if you need it.

The Home Tab

The home tab is the default tab in Visio like most of the Microsoft software. It allows you to change the font, size, color, etc of your drawing and text. If you are familiar with MS Word or Excel, then you might be knowing this well.

The Insert Tab

The insert tab provides you with the options to insert diagram parts, illustrations, links, and text.

The Design Tab

The functions of the design tab include changing the background, the page size, layout, borders, etc.

The Data Tab

Using this tab, you will be able to link your database data with shapes, insert vertical and horizontal legend, and create data graphics.

The Process Tab

The process tab can be used to import and export the workflow and also to link the existing subprocess to a shape in a larger process.

The Review Tab

This tab helps in adding comments and spelling checking.

The View Tab

The tab allows you the personalization of your view of the drawing page. You can add rulers, guides, page breaks, etc.

Steps to creating your first Visio Charts

Step 1) The first step is to have a detailed understanding of what you want to accomplish with all the details. This will help you to come up with a better diagram to draw. You may need to do some research for this.

Step 2) Determine which template best fits your needs. There are many built-in templates available for you to pick from. If you need, you can also pick a chart. It depends on your need.

Step 3) Select the template of your choice.

Step 4) Now drag and connect symbols or shapes. You can use connectors to link between shapes.

Step 5) To add a text box you need to click on the Insert tab, then select the text box, and then select the horizontal-vertical text box according to your need.

Step 6) Last, review your diagram with the draft and make changes if necessary. Save your file.

Wrapping Up

Microsoft Visio is a powerful app that is used for diagramming. It is one of the Microsoft products that is used by many people across the world. The app helps you draw charts, diagrams, flowcharts, and more with an easy-to-access toolbar and friendly navigation. Most of the functions are through drag and drop. This is what makes Visio separate from other similar platforms. Businesses use Visio to increase their productivity and get a better understanding of ideas and processes. It is an app that will help in your business workflow and collaboration. Ideas can be depicted and conclusions can be reached upon by the team members working with Visio. The integration of Visio in Microsoft teams makes it all the more convenient, whereby the team can collaborate in real-time on the diagrams. This Microsoft Visio Tutorial will help you in your understanding and use of Visio. Make a great experience with Visio.
